text: Stary Dwór (formerly German Altenhof) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Trzciel, within Międzyrzecz County, Lubusz Voivodeship, in western Poland. The village has a population of 360. == Geography == Stary Dwór lies about west of Trzciel, south-east of Międzyrzecz, north of Zielona Góra, and south-east of Gorzów Wielkopolski. == Gallery == Stary Dwór.JPG|Stary Dwór Stary Dwór 3.JPG|The Saint Lawrence church == References == Category:Villages in Lubusz Voivodeship
